# ...contenido original de bitácora continúa aquí...

This repository documents the process of learning how to
navigate that new landscape.

------------------------------------------------------------

THE CORE IDEA

Most repositories show the final result.

Clean code.
Finished projects.
Perfect documentation.

But they rarely show the real process behind them:

confusion
experimentation
debugging
architectural thinking
failed attempts
incremental understanding

That invisible layer is where learning actually happens.

This repository tries to document that layer.

------------------------------------------------------------

AI AS A THINKING TOOL

Artificial intelligence is used here as a continuous
technical assistant.

Not as a code generator.

But as a tool for thinking.

The interaction model is based on long-running conversations
about the same technical problems.

Instead of isolated prompts, the AI gradually accumulates
context about:

the systems being built
the tools being used
the concepts being explored

In practice the AI acts as:

technical explainer

architecture discussion partner

debugging assistant

documentation collaborator

research accelerator

But all final decisions remain human.

AI amplifies reasoning.

It does not replace it.

------------------------------------------------------------

THE LEARNING METHOD

The workflow used in this lab is iterative.

Problems are explored through small cycles.

problem appears

↓

question is formulated

↓

AI helps explore explanations

↓

hypotheses are generated

↓

code experiments are implemented

↓

results are evaluated

↓

insights are documented

↓

repeat

Each cycle produces a small piece of understanding.

Over time those pieces accumulate into real skill.

------------------------------------------------------------

DAILY ROUTINE

Typical working session:

1. review previous notes
2. identify a technical question
3. discuss possible explanations with AI
4. test ideas in code
5. observe the results
6. refine the approach
7. document what was learned

Progress is measured in clarity.

Not in speed.

------------------------------------------------------------

AREAS OF EXPLORATION

This lab explores the intersection between:

software engineering

geospatial systems

mineral exploration data

databases and data pipelines

AI-assisted development workflows

The focus is not on mastering tools individually,
but on understanding how systems connect.

------------------------------------------------------------

TOOLS CURRENTLY BEING EXPLORED

Python

PostgreSQL

PostGIS

FastAPI

GeoPandas

Shapely

Git and GitHub

Linux / WSL

These tools are used to experiment with ideas related to
data systems and geospatial workflows.

------------------------------------------------------------

WHY AI MATTERS IN THIS PROCESS

AI dramatically reduces the friction of learning complex
technical subjects.

Instead of spending hours searching fragmented information,
it becomes possible to:

ask precise questions

iterate quickly

test ideas immediately

receive explanations adapted to the current level
of understanding.

This creates a powerful feedback loop between
curiosity and implementation.

------------------------------------------------------------

CONSISTENCY OVER INTENSITY

The biggest variable in learning complex systems
is not intelligence.

It is consistency.

Small focused sessions repeated over time
produce deeper understanding than sporadic bursts
of intense work.

This repository acts as a structure that supports
that consistency.

------------------------------------------------------------

LONG TERM OBJECTIVE

Develop the ability to:

understand complex technical systems

design scalable architectures

build data-driven applications

work with geospatial data pipelines

use AI as a thinking accelerator

and eventually contribute to real-world engineering projects.

------------------------------------------------------------

PHILOSOPHY

build slowly

think deeply

iterate constantly

document everything

------------------------------------------------------------

